---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Pharaoh">
  <article class="space-y-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-text-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary mb-8">Pharaoh</h1>
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed"><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">A headless job runner for AI-assisted development</strong></p>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">Pharaoh is a production runtime for the Ushabti development framework. It enables unattended development workflows by orchestrating the full agent loop — Scribe plans work, Builder implements it, and Overseer reviews the result — with no human in the loop.</p>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">Pharaoh is designed for batch work where development can proceed without real-time interaction. It produces working code, commits results, and reports status entirely through automation.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">What Pharaoh Does</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary ml-4">
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Watches a dispatch directory</strong> for markdown files containing phase prompts</li>
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Executes the Ushabti agent loop</strong>: Scribe plans the phase, Builder implements steps, Overseer reviews the work</li>
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Manages git operations</strong>: creates branches, commits work, and can create pull requests</li>
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Reports status via JSON</strong> written to disk, enabling external monitoring and orchestration</li>
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Runs unattended</strong> with no human interaction required during execution</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">How It Works</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">The workflow is simple:</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary ml-4">
        <li>Drop a markdown file with a phase prompt into the dispatch directory</li>
        <li>Pharaoh picks it up and runs the full development cycle</li>
        <li>Work is committed to a git branch</li>
        <li>Pharaoh returns to idle, watching for the next job</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">All agent execution happens automatically. Pharaoh handles the coordination, git operations, and status reporting.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">Open Source</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">Pharaoh is open source and available on GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/adamrdrew/pharaoh" class="text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary hover:underline">github.com/adamrdrew/pharaoh</a></p>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">Run it via npx:</p>
      <pre class="bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-4 py-2 rounded text-sm text-text-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary overflow-x-auto"><code>npx @adamrdrew/pharaoh serve</code></pre>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
